  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - CLERIC</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>1-8, THE MOST ANNOYING TIME IN YOUR LIFE!(DWARVES)</font> - <small>Akroic DeMonte, Prexus</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>
You poor soul, until level 8 your life will be very boring and mundane. Make sure to train all your point in your perfered melee skill, I normally go with 1 hand blunt in order to use shields.
<p>
First off, start outside the gates Kaladim, kill everything that cons even to you(Bats, snakes, skeletons, ect.).  Do not worry about death, at those lower levels you won't need your spells to heal and buff which won't really be useful until 4th.
<p>
From level 2, stay with blues and mix in an occasional white to give an expo burst.  This will get up your fighting skills, and also killing blues rather then whites reduces downtime and gives you a chance to get a small amount of cash.  Never overlook a decaying skeleton, with the Paladin quest in Kaladim if you aren't going mad finding them you're missing out.
<p>
From 3 on, head on to the newbie area by the docks.  Stick to level 2's(Scarab workers, spiderlings, grunts, skunks).  Scarabs will give some pieces needed for the scarab armor quest which may come in handy looking for better armor.  Also, got nuts killing skunks, though you may reek, skunk glads are highly valiable and can be used for a level 5 spell quest which will save you alot of money and give expo.
<p>
Level 4, stick with anything killable and that gives money.  Being a cleric will mean being poor for the majority of your life.  So this means, more skunks, decaying skeletons, grunts, workers, spiderlings, and even some aviak chicks(Or Karg Chicks).  
<p>
Level 5, new spells.....More to mem, more to mem after death, and more to mem after you die once more.  Unless you find a group for the area past x-roads and 2 houses, don't really bother with memming them.  Though a heal once and again will heal, and so will your newly achieved DD(Furor).  Continue with anything that will give you expo, you can practically melee anything by your level or below.
<p>
If you found a group, I'd recommend the Skeleton ruins left from the docks or goblins in the area around x-roads, both give good expo and descent money for your level.  
<p>
From 6 up, if you havn't moved away from the newbie area its time.  Turn in all your quest related items and see how much more you have to push to 8th.  This is a time in which you need to have yourself fully buffed and as long as your tank, who will quickly become your lifeline.  
<p>
Though at level 7 you can solo skeleton with relative ease, you still can get bone chips which will be valuable in your way to level 8.  But, if you poor of the skeleton, head to the plains and kill everything that you can take, always make sure to con first.  Scarabs are now in your reach with a partner, as well are basilisk though they tend to be more of a headache then a help.
<p>
At level 8, you finally get your beloved meditate.  DROP EVERYTHING AND TRAIN!  You only need to train a point in it but its still handy to pour in a point in two more.  
<p>
At 8, you can continue with the things you were hunting before or you can move on to the chessboard north from the 2 huts.  Though, I'd recommend neither, I'd recommend befriending a necromancer of the same level and head to the mummy camp in lesser fay.  This is the most beautiful expo spot for your level, it can take you from level 8(7 if you are daring and love downtime) to 12 in a matter of hours(Yes, I have too much time on my hands).  And, if you still enjoy the area you can take mummies until 15th, though I'd recommend stopping at 14th due to slow expo progression.
<p>
Questions?  E-mail me at KillerTeddyBear@hotmail.com
I do ask that you don't abuse my kindness:)  </td></tr>
